author: NICK MCMILLION/TIMESNEWSPAPERS
title: Mossville runs at sectionals
text: Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 6:00 AM By NICK MCMILLION/TIMESNEWSPAPERS Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 6:00 AM PEORIA The Mossville Junior High School Warriors cross country team raced in sectionals on Saturday at Donovan Park in Peoria. The Warriors competed against 13 other schools. The girls team finished third behind Elmwood and Princeville. Marley Williamson finished with a time 14:07. Kayla Wolf finished with a time of 14:10. Eve Blanch finished with a time of 14:36. Mikayla Kohlman finished with a time of 14:45. Bronwyn Jetton finished with a time of 15:28. Abby Petran finished with a time of 15:42 and Abi Slater finished with a time of 16:39. The girls team advances to the state meet in Normal. The boys team finished seventh. Collin Eisenbarth finished with a time 12:36. Gabe Ross finished with a time of 13:55. Jayden McNaught finished with a time of 13:56 Nathan Koch finished with a time of 14:43 and Seth Norsworthy 16:05. As a top finisher, who is not on a qualifying team, Collin Eisenbarth earned the right to compete at state. “I love to see them encourage each other and work toward a common goal together,” head coach Michele Stewart said. “It’s an honor to be their coach and to see how they improve each and every meet. They are running at their peak performance level and I’m excited to see how they do next weekend at the State meet.” By NICK MCMILLION/TIMESNEWSPAPERS
